.description.en: The CAS 14-E is designed to provide close air support using its 14mm explosive rounds and high magazine capacity to effectively eliminate hostile personnel. All factions can use this weapon.
The powerful bolt-action SR-7 is capable of eliminating targets from extremely long distances. TR use only.
This high-capacity variant of the M18 Needler is fitted for interceptor variants of the Mosquito fighter craft. TR use only.
The NC08 Mag-Scatter's powerful gauss-propelled shot shells and compact frame make it an excellent close-range sidearm.
This platinum variant of the snub-nosed Underboss revolver features a faster rate of fire and more controllable recoil than the bigger NS-44 Commissioner.  All factions can use NS weapons.
Built off of the Pulsar assault rifle, the long-range Darkstar was named after the notorious squad of designated marksman medics that popularized its use.
Created for spec-ops missions where sniper rifles would prove unsuitable, the powerful semi-automatic Nyx VX31 scout rifle excels at medium range. VS use only.
The Thumper heavy grenade launcher comes equipped with anti-infantry fragmentation rounds, and has access to multiple specialized munitions. All factions can use this weapon.
The anti-air NS-10 Burster uses Smart Unguided Projectiles to explode in the presence of ferrous material at high speeds. NC use only.
The M20 Kestrel couples a large magazine size with no damage falloff, allowing it to perform well against enemy aircraft at long range. NC use only.
The P2-120-R HEAT carries quick-reloading high-explosive anti-tank rounds that have balanced effectiveness against armor and infantry. TR use only.
Focusing on high rate of fire and deadly precision, Tomoe rewards headhunters, making it a desirable option for mid-range assassinations. All factions can use NS weapons.

During focus group testing, the compact, automatic, NSX Yawara pistol was overlooked at nearly every turn, failing to reach the popularity of the numerous other Nanite Systems pistol designs released throughout the Auraxian War.
This black, left-handed NS-10 Burster fires flak rounds which detonate near enemy aircraft, shredding their armor. All factions can use NS weapons.
The M2's increased ammo capacity has proven itself as a boon to small or stranded squads. TR use only.
The Coyote Missile platform's proximity-based homing missiles excel at destroying lightly armored aircraft, but are less proficient at harming heavily armored targets. NC use only.
This gold left-handed NS-20 Gorgon is a slow firing heavy machine gun effective at eliminating armored targets, but can challenge close-range infantry as well. All factions can use NS weapons.
The automatic SOAS-20's high rate of fire makes it an excellent choice for mid-range encounters. TR use only.
The bolt-action XM98's dialed-in power core interface draws allows for a remarkably versatile plasma sniper rifle. VS use only.
A popular choice among Engineers and Light Assaults, the NS-11CB is an accurate and stable all-around performer. This variant of the 11C has a black metal finish. All factions can use NS weapons.
The G30 Walker is a heavy machine gun with a high elevation range and soft point ammunition designed to be more effective against aircraft. VS use only.
Vanu Esamir's weapon labs created the Solstice Burst to further extend the weapon's range with a controlled burst fire mode. VS use only.
The Python HESH carries high-explosive squash head rounds that are less effective against armor, and more lethal against enemy infantry. All factions can use this weapon.

This platinum MKV has an integrated suppressor that prevents the user from showing on the minimap when firing. It features superior bullet velocity and long range stopping power compared to SMGs using optional aftermarket suppressors. All factions can use NS weapons.
The Basilisk is a 20mm heavy machine gun that effectively damages all targets, especially at close range. VS use only.

The Butcher gained its reputation as a fearsome weapon capable of unending, long-range suppressive fire following a series of extended engagements at The Crown. Built on the CARV platform, the Butcher's notoriety has been earned over time in blood.

The semi-automatic Special Purpose Rifle (SPR) is a marksman rifle built on the highly-configurable Gauss platform. Developed after the start of the Auraxis War, it has remained in use due to its accuracy when making long-distance shots. NC use only.
Recoil dampeners throughout the hefty Phantom VA23 make pulling off medium-range follow up shots effortless. VS use only.

The Pulsar Light Support Weapon (LSW) is a Pulsar variant with a high capacity battery and heavier barrel. Its reputation as a highly versatile weapon makes it a popular choice for missions where anything can happen. VS use only.

The Yumi burst rifle is capable of, after a short delay, unleashing a rapid five round volley. With proper shot placement, Yumi can strike down mid-range targets more quickly than most weapons in its class. All factions can use NS weapons.
Before being retired during the early years of the war, the Suppressor was used for low-profile infiltration missions where engagements could take place in tight corridors.
The Basilisk is a 20mm heavy machine gun that effectively damages all targets, especially at close range. NC use only.
Based on a modified Fracture design, the Gatekeeper retains the feel of its forerunner but incorporates a faster fire rate and projectile speed while increasing overall accuracy.
Co-developed with Genudine's Offense Development team, the NC6A GODSAW incorporates an alternate firing mode which allows the weapon to pierce heavy armor in exchange for reduced infantry damage.
The Basilisk is a 20mm heavy machine gun that effectively damages all targets, especially at close range. TR use only.

Horizon's experimental design fires a fan of three projectiles on a horizontal trajectory when hipfiring, and a tighter, vertical trajectory when aiming. Each plasma projection packs less firepower than the average carbine individually, but when all projections land, the stopping power rivals that of harder hitting weapons. VS use only.
The SMG-46 Armistice fully automatic submachine gun features an extremely fast rate of fire. TR use only.
The powerful and accurate Reaper DMR was developed to fulfill the needs of soldiers who prefer to provide support from a distance. NC use only.
The bulky EM4 Longshot's overclocked propulsion coils allow for projectiles that both travel faster and hit harder in comparison to other bolt-action sniper rifles. NC use only.

The 11AG is the gold high-end variant of the adaptable 11A assault rifle platform. Reliable with a wide assortment of attachments, the 11AG can change itself to excel in nearly any situation. All factions can use NS weapons.
The sound of the menacing T7 MCG firing strikes fear into the heart of its enemies. It is capable of sustained fire that can tear apart entire squads. TR use only.
Advances in plasma manipulation technology have resulted in the VE-S Canis, a compact, close range weapon with a firing rate that increases over time. VS use only.
Utilizing an energy efficient power core interface, the experimental Phobos VX86 is able to provide sustained fire before needing a new battery. VS use only.
Named for the pandemonium this highly modified plasma-core shotgun can cause in a surprise ambush, the Chaos' reputation as a very deadly flanking weapon has been well earned.
The NS-11CP's compact frame makes it a viable close range option over its predecessor, the NS-11P, and just as effective as the original NS-11C.  All factions can use NS weapons.

Nanite Systems' mightiest anti-tank weapon received a facelift with the release of The Kraken, a commemorative Auraxium-plated Decimator. Its powerful warheads create a miniaturized singularity upon impact.

The NC's A-Tross was created as the ultimate in heavy-hitting, long-range assault rifles. Featuring a 30-round magazine and an overclocked propulsion coil firing a high-damage projectile, the A-Tross can drop targets at even distant ranges.

The Lancer AE's particle accelerator is capable of firing a focused, high-velocity anti-armor projectile with pinpoint accuracy. The weapon has three charge-levels which increases damage and ammunition used. VS use only.
The TR released the Unity to commemorate the time-tested Cycler assault rifle, a key weapon attributed to helping bring Earth together under the Terran Republic's harmonious rule.

The dumbfire-capable T2 Striker houses a six-round magazine of compact, heat-seeking rockets that will home in when within proximity of enemy aircraft. TR use only. <font color="#dc9c36">Flak detonation. Proximity Seeking: Aircraft</font>
This black right-handed NS-20 Gorgon is a slow firing heavy machine gun effective at eliminating armored targets, but can challenge close-range infantry as well. All factions can use NS weapons.

Unlike its Yumi predecessor, the NSX Kuwa will, after a short windup, release a torrent of accurate, high caliber rounds down range until the trigger is released. This weapon is a hybrid rifle, available to Engineer, Combat Medic, and Heavy Assault classes.
The anti-air NS-10 Burster uses Smart Unguided Projectiles to explode in the presence of ferrous material at high speeds. TR use only.
The EM6's incredible adaptability on the field makes it popular among NC soldiers. NC use only.
Many TR soldiers praise the Terran Assault Rifle's performance in the field, crediting many victories to its incredible hip fire accuracy and high rate of fire. TR use only.
The powerful Hunter QCX Quad-Cam crossbow is a lightweight sidearm, capable of silently taking out targets up to medium range with deadly precise bolts.
The TS2 Inquisitor features an extended magazine capable of outlasting the enemy even in the most drawn out firefights. TR use only.

The left-handed NS-20 Gorgon is a slow firing, heavy machine gun effective at eliminating armored targets, and can challenge close-range infantry as well. This variant features classy flames over a black finish. All factions can use NS weapons.
The M14 Banshee is a high speed gatling gun that fires explosive 14mm rounds, excellent for dealing with enemy infantry and light vehicles. TR use only.
The G30 Walker is a heavy machine gun with a high elevation range and soft point ammunition designed to be more effective against aircraft. All factions can use this weapon.
The burst fire variant of the TRAC-5 provides accurate and controllable firepower suitable for any number of situations. TR use only.
The arm-mounted NCM1 Scattercannon functions as a semi-automatic shotgun capable of cutting through enemy squads. NC use only.
The Fury launches 40mm grenades that are effective against infantry and light armor.  It is also capable of light damage against heavy armor.  All factions can use this weapon.

Vanu Esamir's AdvWep labs designed the heavy-hitting Flare VE6 to pack the most punch per shot. In the hands of an experience marksman, the Flare can wreak havoc on enemy infantry at close to medium ranges. VS use only.
The Buzzard converts the flash into a makeshift artillery platform, using heavy high explosive shells with a large blast radius. NC use only.
Your targets can't avoid their date with the Gallows forever...
This 4th Anniversary Edition of the compact GR-22 has improved handling when firing on the move, making it an excellent choice for close quarters combat. NC use only.
The LA8 Rebel's high damage gives it a longer effective range when compared to most side arms. NC use only.
The Pelter Rocket Pod launches a barrage of unguided anti-armor rockets which have little explosive yield. All factions can use this weapon.
The Skyguard fires 40mm flak rounds that are highly effective against enemy aircraft. All factions can use this weapon.
Breaker Rocket Pods fire a volley of up to 12 unguided, high-explosive rockets. NC use only.

This variant of the Archer Anti-Materiel Rifle was designed to operate at closer distances, relying on snappy close range optics and quicker draw times in exchange for long range power and magazine size.
The M60 Bulldog fires high explosive 60mm rounds with a large blast radius effective against infantry.  Direct hits provides some damage to armor. All factions can use this weapon.

Built from a highly-tinkered Parallax, the Parsec was the brainchild of a small group of engineers looking for long-range perfection. Though significantly louder than most sniper rifles, it drops targets before the sound wave even reaches them.
The T16 Rhino was designed as a squad support weapon that remains accurate, even during sustained fire. TR use only.
The Gauss Rifle S possesses a select fire option that allows for further adaptability on the battlefield. NC use only.
The Pillager lays down a field of flames which ignite infantry caught within. TR use only.

The L-24R Spur is equipped with specialized optics that allow the pilot to adjust the weapons aim rather than being fixed forward.

Optics for this weapon are engaged with Weapon Optic function or Cockpit Mouse Freelook hotkeys.
The M6 Onslaught was designed as a defensive alternative to the MX1, allowing for a higher rate of fire suitable for holding down important locations. TR use only.

Orion's largest star also shines brightly as a powerful, accurate LMG capable of sustained suppressing fire. Plagued by multiple redesigns during its troubled development, the third and final iteration proved itself as a favorite amongst the VS.
The semi-automatic Impetus sniper rifle is a favorite amongst Infiltrators for covert operations. It excels at medium range due to its considerable stopping power and rate of fire. NC use only.
Designed for raw power, this black variant of the Decimator is unmatched in its destructive potential against enemy vehicles and infantry. All factions can use NS weapons.

Equipped with an experimental regenerating power core, the Phaseshift VX-S has no use for traditional ammunition, and can switch between semi-auto and bolt-action firing modes to fit the engagement range. VS use only.
This gold, left-handed NS-10 Burster fires flak rounds which detonate near enemy aircraft, shredding their armor. All factions can use NS weapons.
The Eridani SX5 fully automatic submachine gun excels in close quarter combat situations. VS use only.
The AF-19 Mercenary became the standard issue carbine for the NC due to its low production costs. It features controllable recoil that makes it effective at close to medium ranges. NC use only.
The Maelstrom is a high damage, fast firing nose cannon which tears apart enemy fighters at close range. VS use only.
This 4th Anniversary Edition Eridani SX5 submachine gun excels in close quarter combat situations. VS use only.

The 99SV is the standard issue semi-automatic sniper rifle of TR Infiltrators. An accurized variant of the DMR-99, the 99SV allows the shooter to hit multiple follow-up shots at long range. TR use only.
The Supernova VPC is charged with volatile high-explosive plasma that is less effective against armor, and more lethal to enemy personnel. VS use only.
The powerful TS4 Haymaker features a large magazine, allowing for sustained fire without needing to reload. TR use only.
The P2-120 HESH is loaded with high-explosive squash head rounds that are less effective against armor, but more lethal to enemy infantry. TR use only.
The versatile standard-issue NC4 Mag-Shot was the first pistol to utilize Gauss technology. NC use only.
The AF-34 Mattock features increased effective range in comparison to the other MAX anti-infantry weapons. NC use only.
The T1S Cycler performs well at many ranges, attributing its adaptability due to its multiple fire modes. TR use only.
The Beamer VS3 is the standard sidearm for the Vanu Sovereignty. Its high rate of fire allows the user to eliminate nearby targets quickly. VS use only.
The M18 Locust incorporates a large magazine and steady damage over distance, allowing it to engage enemy aircraft from beyond their reach. TR use only.

This 4th Anniversary Edition of the EM4 Longshot houses an overclocked propulsion coil for projectiles that both travel faster and hit harder in comparison to other bolt-action sniper rifles. NC use only.
A precursor to the Tengu SMG, the NSX Kappa spits out three heavy pellets per shot, and was the first SMG to integrate a smart choke system that tightens pellet spread while aiming down sights.
The T5 AMC's damage output and controllable recoil was designed around giving Terran Republic soldiers increased effectiveness in medium range encounters. TR use only.

A late successor to the Quasar VM1, the Cosmos uses experimental plasma containment technology, resulting in larger rounds. These large plasma rounds cause less cranial trauma, but are significantly easier to strike mobile targets with. VS use only.
The Coyote Missile platform's proximity-based homing missiles excel at destroying lightly armored aircraft, but are less proficient at harming heavily armored targets. VS use only.

The right-handed NS-20 Gorgon is a slow firing, heavy machine gun effective at eliminating armored targets, and can challenge close-range infantry as well. This variant features classy flames over a black finish. All factions can use NS weapons.
The Titan-150 HESH is loaded with high-explosive squash head rounds that sacrifice some effectiveness against armor for increased lethality to enemy personnel. NC use only.
Custom-built for Sigma Squad's infamous Hossin Rebirth mission, the unique Tempest SMG performs similar as a carbine at long distances.
The 4th Anniversary Edition AF-4 Cyclone submachine gun offers higher damage output than most weapons in its class. NC use only.
The Antares LC's large magazine and steady damage allows pilots to maintain a constant stream of anti-aircraft fire from a safe distance. VS use only.
The versatile T1B Cycler is nearly identical to the original, with an added accurate burst fire mode. TR use only.

The Lancer VS22's particle accelerator is capable of firing a focused, high-velocity anti-armor projectile with pinpoint accuracy. The weapon has three charge-levels which increases damage and ammunition used. VS use only.
The Deimos VA29 is one of Vanu Amerish's most popular shotguns. Its high damage energy shells mow through enemy soldiers at a frightening pace. VS use only.
The Cerberus is able to fire overcharged rounds that are highly damaging in close range. VS use only.

Built off of the NS-11, the NS-15M2 is an accurate, magazine-fed LMG that leaves little downtime during reloads. Its reputation as a reliable all-arounder makes it suitable for many types of combat situations. All factions can use NS weapons.
Developed for a mix of close quarters combat and point defense, the T32 Bull features both balanced recoil and high maneuverability. TR use only.
Liberty Arsenal forged this special variant of the LA1 Anchor in recognition of the weapon's long-term performance in the hands of a skillful operator.

Genudine's heavily modified Guardian rifle was initially designed for long-range support for Heavy Assault soldiers ambushing from on high or in cover. Deadly from even long distances, the accurate Guardian can drop targets from afar with ammo to spare.
The Solar-1 rocket launcher fires a bolt of superheated plasma capable of melting infantry, MAXes and vehicle armor. VS use only.

The TR's infamous Havoc Squad popularized this shotgun loadout enough to have it put into production. Primarily used with behind-the-lines galaxy drops to secure CCs, the Havoc can clear rooms and hold points with the best of them.

The gold finish on the NS-15MG has cemented it as a status symbol among soldiers on Auraxis. Good looks aside, the 15MG is an accurate all-arounder that performs well in many combat situations. All factions can use NS weapons.

Genudine Dynamics developed the 22S as a possible replacement for the NC6 SAW. In comparison to the SAW, it features a faster firing rate and reload time, but is limited by a 50-round detachable box magazine. NC use only.

Nanite Systems' launched the tube-fed Baron G5 shotgun to help round out their extensive arsenal. Decked out with a special orange stripe paintjob, the Baron G5AE performs well at ranges typical shotguns become ineffective. All factions can use NS weapons.
G20 Vulcan-H fires armor piercing 20mm rounds capable of damaging heavily armored targets. TR use only.
The MSW-R was designed to meet the needs of mobile Terran Republic shock troopers. Its light weight and fast reload time allows forward soldiers to push forward without stopping. TR use only.

The LA1 Anchor is tuned for close quarters effectiveness. It features high damage, moderate rate of fire, advanced laser attachments, and a 50 round box magazine for quick combat reloads. NC use only.

The TRs' Bighorn .50M surpassed the RAMS as the heaviest sniper rifle in their arsenal. Boasting an unmatched bullet velocity and a straight-pull bolt for rapid shots, the deafening crack of the Bighorn is a warning to distant soldiers.
The 2-round burst LA3 Desperado can quickly eliminate targets at close range. NC use only.
The P2-120 HEAT carries quick-reloading high-explosive anti-tank rounds that have balanced effectiveness against armor and infantry. TR use only.
The VX6-7's fast rate of fire and lightweight construction make it an excellent weapon in close quarters combat. VS use only.
The playful Tengu SMG scatters four pellets per shot, and narrows its pellet spread while aiming down sights. All factions can use NS weapons.
The Lacerta assault rifle syncs an accurate, three round burst to a moderate refire rate, and creates a melodic barrage of plasma, perfect for mid-range engagements. VS use only.
Reminescent of old-world deringer designs, this modified Underboss fires two rounds at once.
The TAS-16 Blackjack boasts extremely high close quarters burst damage, even for a shotgun. TR use only.
Play with the hearts of your enemies (?) using this lovingly crafted Archer Anti-Materiel rifle variant. All factions can use NS weapons.

Designed with mobility in mind, the lightweight alloys that make up Auraxis Firearm's AF-A4 Bandit allows for faster movement while aiming without compromising on stopping power in close to medium ranges.
The E540 Halberd fires 85 mm armor-piercing rockets. TR use only.
The Enforcer ML85 fires magnetically propelled HEAT darts, suited for sustained damage in mid-range combat scenarios. NC use only.
The NC2S Gauss Compact possesses a select-fire mode that further diversifies the usage of the already adaptable carbine. NC use only.

Cutting edge railgun tech found in Auraxis' Firearms Railjack sniper rifle allows for lightning-fast bullet velocities. Distant targets are dropped almost instantly following a split-second charge-up delay from its powerful superconductor.
The fully automatic Artemis VX26 scout rifle is capable of quickly dispatching enemy infantry at close to medium ranges. VS use only.
The reliable TX1 Repeater's 3-round burst fire mode provides considerable stopping power at close range. This variant features a unique gold plating.  TR use only.
Modeled after the popular 11A, the 11C carbine is a stable and accurate all-arounder, making it a great choice for engagements up to medium ranges. All factions can use NS weapons.
The L-30R Vektor is accurate but slow firing and can pierce all types of armor. All factions can use this weapon.
Designed for raw power, this gold plated variant of the Decimator is unmatched in its destructive potential against enemy vehicles and infantry. All factions can use NS weapons.
This 4th Anniversary Edition of the Terran Assault Rifle credits many victories to its incredible hip fire accuracy and high rate of fire. TR use only.

The NSX Sesshin was intended as a multi-class platform that filled an aggressive, mid-long range combat role, though it was eventually set aside as company resources shifted in favor of developing the Daimyo and Tomoe.

The C75 is able to rapid fire six 75mm HEAT shells.  The damage potential is great when all shells hit their target, but the cannon is unstable when firing at the maximum rate. All factions can use this weapon.
The Archer anti-materiel rifle was developed by Nanite Systems to counter the heavily armored MAX, providing an effective option at range for dealing with the unique threat of the exo-suits.
The semi-automatic AMR-66 battle rifle uses powerful cartridges that hold considerable stopping power up to medium range. TR use only.
The S12 Renegade is an effective shotgun that is lethal to soft targets at close range. All factions can use this weapon.
This lucky launcher has the full functionality of Nanite Systems' Decimator revisited with green and gold stylings. All factions can use this weapon.

The Rocklet Rifle fires munitions that auto-det on aircraft or pierce enemy ground vehicle armor. Alternate rocklet types may be loaded into the weapon.

Press Aim Down Sights to fire a rocklet barrage.
Very few weapons are able to touch the Lynx's incredible rate of fire. Featuring a cyclic rate of 909 RPM, the LC2 Lynx tears through infantry at close to medium range.

This hard hitting but slower firing SMG is used as an efficient personal defense weapon with a solid gold finish.  Made by Nanite Systems, the leading Auraxis firearms dealer. All factions can use NS weapons.
The P2-120 AP is loaded with fast-moving armor piercing rounds that are stronger against armored targets, but have less explosive yield than other projectiles. TR use only.

The Auraxium variant of the NC4, The Executive is typically only issued to the enigmatic members of The Board, the New Conglomerate's governing body. It features a unique low-velocity suppressor that doesn't affect stopping power at range.

The Cycler TRV's fast rate of fire makes it extremely effective in close quarters, though that same rate of fire and high recoil limits its effectiveness at long range when firing in full-auto. TR use only.
Deadly in the hands of a skilled Infiltrator, the bolt action TSAR-42's features a unique bolt rotation system designed to improve the time between shots. TR use only.
Vanu Esamir Labs created the Equinox VE2 Burst to provide easily controllable burst fire for distant targets. VS use only.
Equipped with a state of the art cooling jacket, the Watchman LMG boasts the highest rate of fire of any weapon in its class. TR use only.
Designed as an alternative to the popular SABR-13 assault rifle, the Arbalest fires concentrated, 6-round bursts with low recoil and high takedown potential at mid-range. TR use only.
The Prowler M12 Kobalt is a .50 cal machine gun that is effective against infantry targets. TR use only.
The G40-F Ranger is an air deterrent flak cannon.  It has a high elevation range and launches 40mm flak rounds that burst when near enemy aircraft. VS use only.
The Nebula VM20's overclocked power core interface allows for a rapid rate of fire to quickly dispatch enemy infantry in close quarters. VS use only.

The NS-15M AE is an accurate, magazine-fed LMG that leaves little downtime during reloads. This commemorative edition of the popular all-arounder LMG features an exclusive orange stripe paintjob. All factions can use NS weapons.
Equipped with a built-in extended magazine, the Blitz GD-10's increased ammo capacity enables it to put down multiple targets between reloads. NC use only.
The medium-range SAS-R's sniper rifle features a rapid bolt action that allows users to make follow up shots on targets before they can reach cover. NC use only.

Though not officially sanctioned for use on the field, the TR has turned a blind eye to the use of the TRAC-Shot. Bolted together by TR mechanics in their downtime, the TRAC-Shot's multiple rail attachments are unconventional but effective.

The Hades VSH4 anti-armor launcher can lock onto ground vehicles and deliver a heavy burst of damage, and retains its dumbfire capability for close range situations. VS use only. <font color="#dc9c36">Optional Lockon: Armor</font>
The NS-11A was designed as a customizable weapon system that could adapt to nearly every situation. This variant features classy flames over a black finish. All factions can use NS weapons.
The NS-11P is a platinum variant of the NS-11A.  Its large, rapid-reload magazine and high-velocity cartridges complement its variety of attachments. All factions can use NS weapons.

The dumbfire-capable Striker AE houses a six-round magazine of compact, heat-seeking rockets that will home in when within proximity of enemy aircraft. TR use only. <font color="#dc9c36">Flak detonation. Proximity Seeking: Aircraft</font>
The Magrider M12 Kobalt is a .50 cal machine gun that is effective against infantry targets. VS use only.

The SVA-88's overclocked discharge coil allows it to fire plasma at a higher velocity than most weapons in its class. When firing at long distances, the user will need to lead targets much less than usual. VS use only.
Auraxis Firearms' first venture into MAX weaponry was the AF-23 Grinder. It features an extended ammo reserve for sustained fire. NC use only.
The AF-6 Shadow is a semi-automatic scout rifle purpose-built for closer effective ranges than sniper rifles. NC use only.
The Ghost VS12's high rate of fire provides considerable lethality at medium range due to its modified heat-shunting discharge coil. VS use only.
This 4th Anniversary Edition Archer anti-material rifle was developed by Nanite Systems to dispatch MAX-based threats at medium to long range.
The powerful Heartstring Quad-Cam crossbow is a lightweight sidearm, capable of silently taking out targets up to medium range with deadly precise bolts.

Released as a commemorative edition of the NC's wildly successful foray into electromagnetic weaponry, the NC1 Gauss Rifle, the Gauss Prime marksman assault rifle can effortlessly drop distant targets.
The lightweight Blueshift VM5 anti-infantry MAX weapon was designed to provide increased accuracy over the standard-issue VM1. VS use only.
The P525 Marauder-H fires 40mm high explosive grenades that are effective against infantry and light armor. TR use only.
The Promise LMG's large magazine and high rate of fire are complemented by in-built counterweights for sustained accuracy. NC use only.
The Beamer VS3 is the standard sidearm for the Vanu Sovereignty. Its high rate of fire allows the user to eliminate nearby targets quickly. This variant features a unique gold plating.  VS use only.
The C85 fires a canister of heavy shrapnel that is effective against infantry and light armor. NC use only.
A popular sidearm amongst TR soldiers, the high-capacity TX2 Emperor has been in service for over 200 years. TR use only.
The CME's high projectile velocity and good accuracy make it a very effective weapon at medium and long ranges. VS use only.

The magazine-fed NS-R3 Swarm can switch between low velocity and high velocity rockets which lock onto both ground and air targets, allowing the user to tailor the weapon's tracking capabilities based on the engagement. <font color="#dc9c36">Flak detonation.  Required Lockon: Aircraft or Armor</font>
Manufactured with an energy-efficient discharge coil, the high capacity Nova is capable of extended fire before needing to change power cores. VS use only.
The Coyote Missile platform's proximity-based homing missiles excel at destroying lightly armored aircraft, but are less proficient at harming heavily armored targets. TR use only.
The high muzzle velocity of the LA80's projectiles reduces the amount that a target must be lead, making it an excellent choice for sniping targets at extreme distances. NC use only.
The Hornet Missiles are laser guided and will fly towards the pilot's crosshairs.  TR use only.

The high velocity plasma projectiles the Vanu Sovereignty's V10 fires reduces the amount that moving targets must be lead, making it one of the easiest to use long range weapons on Auraxis. VS use only.
The G30 Walker is a heavy machine gun with a high elevation range and soft point ammunition designed to be more effective against aircraft. NC use only.
The Obelisk long rifle makes up for its slow rate of fire with hard hitting rounds and a heat-based ammo pool. VS use only.
Auraxis Firearms launched the Fortuna Mercenary for the discerning soldier of fortune that prefers close-quarters combat without having to give up their shotgun.
The NC6 Gauss SAW's low production cost, reliability, and sheer stopping power lead to wide-spread adoption of the weapon in the Auraxian War's early years. NC use only.

This special, versatile variant of the CARV can adapt to nearly any situation thanks to its multiple firing modes and wide range of attachments. Compared to its predecessor, it features a slightly slower rate of fire and more controllable recoil. TR use only.
The automatic AF-18 Stalker is deadly in close quarters and medium range combat. NC use only.
Boasting a longer barrel than its compact Light Carbine cousin, the mobile LC3 Jaguar was designed to provide accurate hip fire at longer distances than the Lynx. TR use only.
The powerful Phoenix AE uses a camera guided missile that allows the user to adjust its trajectory mid-flight. NC use only.

Though currently not in production, the Terran Republic's powerful DMR-99 has a dedicated following of designated marksmen that stick by their tried-and-true battle rifle, rather than switch to a newer model.
The Hammerhead anti-materiel rifle revisits the power of the trusted NS-AM7 Archer, while bringing with it a more striking and modern visual design.
The TRS-12 Uppercut's highly mobile platform provides great versatility and speed while engaging multiple targets. TR use only.
This 4th Anniversary Edition of the RAMS .50 harnesses high muzzle velocity and stopping power to hit harder and faster than other sniper rifles in its class. TR use only.
Affectionately referred to as "The Boombox" by many NC soldiers, the Mjolnir's burst fire explosive rounds excel against armored targets in close quarters engagements.
This 4th Anniversary Edition of the Parallax VX3 is a heavy-hitting, high velocity sniper rifle, allowing for easy long distance shots. VS use only.
Chambered for the powerful 12.7x75mm round, the high muzzle velocity and stopping power afforded by the RAMS .50M ensures shots will hit harder and faster than others in its class. TR use only.
The standard issue NC1 Gauss Rifle was the first successful implementation of coilgun technology in small arms. NC use only.
Liberty Arsenal's flagship pump shotgun, the LA39 Bruiser is designed to inflict massive damage on infantry targets. NC use only.
Designed with a lightning-quick receiver, the fully-automatic AS16 Nighthawk features a higher rate of fire than typical shotguns. TR use only.

The Terran Republic's Heavy Carbine project resulted in the HC1 Cougar. Utilizing a higher caliber cartridge than its LC cousins, the Cougar possesses unparalleled stopping power amongst other Terran carbines up to medium range.
The Supernova PC quickly reloads its high-explosive anti-tank plasma charges that carry balanced effectiveness against armor and infantry. VS use only.
The M12 Kobalt is a .50 cal machine gun that is effective against infantry targets. All factions can use this weapon.
Originally reserved for members of Nomad, the Gladius is the hardest hitting SMG ever designed. NC use only.
Esamir Munition Corporation's EM1 LMG is a unique mix of high ammo count and fast reloading time, allowing the shooter to control firing lanes with little downtime. NC use only.
Advanced cooling techniques provide the Maw LMG with a decisive mix of reload speed and stopping power, offering flexibility in many combat scenarios. VS use only.
The versatile Equinox VE2 assault rifle was designed to perform well in many situations. VS use only.
The Gauss Rifle Burst features the same versatility as the NC1, but with an easily controllable burst fire mode. NC use only.
The unguided Shrike rocket launcher is equipped with high-explosive warheads and has both anti-personnel and anti-armor capabilities. NC use only.
The M18 Needler is the standard air superiority nose cannon for the TR Mosquito.  Its small caliber rounds allow it to sustain fire for longer and at a higher fire rate.  TR use only.
The M18 Rotary's high firing rate allows it to shred enemy fighters at short range. TR use only.
The anti-air NS-10 Burster uses Smart Unguided Projectiles to explode in the presence of ferrous material at high speeds. VS use only.

Nanite Systems' Annihilator was the first rocket launcher to integrate both air and ground-based lockon capabilities, at cost to its dumbfire capabilities. This variant of the weapon sports a sleek black finish. All factions can use NS weapons. <font color="#dc9c36">Flak detonation. Required Lockon: Aircraft or Armor</font>
The Kindred carbine fires high caliber rounds quickly on trigger press, and then settles into a more rhythmic firing rate after a short time. For TR use only.
An energy efficient power core interface allows the Sirius SX12 to take out multiple targets before needing to reload. VS use only.

The fully automatic NS-61G Emissary operates comfortably at mid-range, thanks to its accuracy and large magazine. This variant of the NS-61 features a stylish gold finish. All factions can use this weapon.
The L105 Zephyr fires a salvo of 105mm high-explosive rounds which are effective against both armor and personnel. All factions can use this weapon.

The SVA-GG's overclocked discharge coil allows it to fire plasma at a higher velocity than most weapons in its class. When firing at long distances, the user will need to lead targets much less than usual. VS use only.
The M202 Wyrm wing-mounted machine guns fire slow, high-damage rounds most effective against heavily armored land and air vehicles.
The Proton II PPA fires large orbs of volatile plasma that explode on impact.  The PPA is effective against infantry and light armor. VS use only.
The Supernova FPC is charged with fast-moving armor-piercing plasma that is more effective against armored targets and inflicts less explosive damage. VS use only.
The Vanguard M12 Kobalt is a .50 cal machine gun that is effective against infantry targets. NC use only.
The Thanatos VE70's lethality in close quarters makes it a frightening opponent in urban combat scenarios. VS use only.
Equipped with an extended magazine, the Hailstorm's generous ammo capacity has saved many soldiers who would've been caught reloading without it. TR use only.
The powerful NC15 Phoenix uses a camera guided missile that allows the user to adjust its trajectory mid-flight. NC use only.

Based off of its bigger assault rifle brother, the smaller Pulsar C  was developed with an emphasis on stopping power. While not as easy to control, the heavy-hitting Pulsar C is far more devastating at close range. VS use only.
The AP30 Shredder machine gun is capable of inflicting sustained and accurate damage with its 30mm armor piercing rounds.  All factions can use this weapon.
The semi-automatic Mauler S6's overclocked propulsion coils and tighter spread make it a versatile close-range weapon. NC use only.
The Hornet Missiles are laser guided and will fly towards the pilot's crosshairs.  VS use only.
The fully automatic NS-61B Emissary operates comfortably at mid-range, thanks to its accuracy and large magazine. This variant of the NS-61 features a black finish. All factions can use this weapon.

The VLG fires a laser guided missile that seeks toward the gunner's crosshairs. The missile is effective against armor on direct hits and produces a moderate blast. Missile will detonate after traveling 400 meters. All factions can use this weapon.

Genudine Dynamics released the highly mobile Claw GD-66 shotgun early in the 29th century. Its lightweight action allows for a higher rate of fire than other pump-action shotguns on the market. NC use only.
The M20-W is a high-capacity variant of the standard M20 Mustang nosegun, meant for use specifically with interceptor setups of the Reaver VTOL fighter. NC use only.
The E540 Halberd fires 85 mm armor-piercing rockets. VS use only.
The M20 Mustang is the standard air superiority nose cannon for the NC Reaver.  Its high caliber rounds allow it to do more damage up close and at range.  NC use only.
The TRAP-M1 can switch between short-range 3-round burst and long-range 2-round burst firing modes, allowing for incredible flexibility on the battlefield.
The A30 Walker is a heavy machine gun with soft point ammunition designed to be more effective against enemy aircraft. All factions can use this weapon.

Scrapped prior to release in favor of the Masamune's wire-guidance system and contextual firing modes, the NSX Muramasa can fire up to four accurate, high damage rockets either from the hip or while aiming down the optics.
The Pulsar VS1 is the standard issue assault rifle for the Vanu Sovereignty. Its low recoil design allows it to remain effective in most situations. VS use only.
The E540 Halberd fires 85mm armor-piercing rockets. All factions can use this weapon.
The NC2B Gauss Compact features a burst fire mode for controllable long range fire. NC use only.
Hellfire Rocket Pods fire a volley of up to 16 unguided, high-explosive rockets. TR use only.
The iconic NC12 Sweeper shotgun features a high capacity magazine as well as considerable stopping power at close range. It excels in urban combat scenarios. NC use only.
This hard hitting but slower firing SMG is used as an efficient personal defense weapon.  Made by Nanite Systems, the leading Auraxis firearms dealer. All factions can use NS weapons.
The Hornet Missiles are laser guided and will fly towards the pilot's crosshairs.  NC use only.
The C150 Dalton fires 150mm Armor Piercing Anti-Tank rounds that inflict massive damage in a single shot. All factions can use this weapon.

This Auraxium-clad variant of the TX1 Repeater is a replica of former Terran Republic President Connery's weapon of choice. Equipped with a special suppressor, this silenced pistol remains effective even at longer ranges.
Embedded recoil dampeners along the barrel of the Polaris allow it to remain accurate when firing from the hip. VS use only.
The Terran Republic's Automatic Machine Pistol functions similarly to an SMG thanks to its lightning-fast, fully automatic fire.
This gold right-handed NS-20 Gorgon is a slow firing heavy machine gun effective at eliminating armored targets, but can challenge close-range infantry as well. All factions can use NS weapons.

The Orion VS54 is the standard issue LMG for Vanu Heavy Assault soldiers. Its lightweight construction allows for more accurate hip fire and stability when on the move when compared to most weapons in its class. VS use only.

Masamune integrates contextual firemodes, allowing it to release all four rockets from the hip, or laser guide them in a burst while using the cutting edge tracking optics. All players can use NS weapons.
Dual Photon Pods fire a volley of up to 14 unguided, high-explosive photon rockets. VS use only.

The Hellion G20 chain gun fires special armor piercing 20mm rounds that are effective against vehicles at close range. It takes 1.5 seconds for the G20 to spool up and reach full firing speed. All factions can use this weapon.
The Titan-150 AP is loaded with fast moving armor piercing rounds that are stronger against armored targets but inflict almost no explosive damage. NC use only.
The L105 Zephyr PX fires a salvo of 105mm high-explosive rounds which are effective against both armor and personnel. All factions can use this weapon.
The Light PPA is a slow-firing plasma cannon that inflicts massive damage at close range. VS use only.
With an extended barrel and integrated scope the NS-44L Blackhand provides significant advantages over similar pistols when engaging threats at longer ranges.
The Saron HRB fires a fast and accurate armor damaging particle beam. Accuracy destabilizes for a split second after each shot.  VS use only.
The Hyena fires short range anti-aircraft missiles that are dumb-fired, but will lock-on to enemy aircraft in close proximity. This weapon specializes in combating mobile enemy fighters.
This platinum variant of the remarkably accurate NS-15M LMG provides excellent sustained fire and above average projectile speed. All factions can use NS weapons.

Auraxis Firearms' first infantry-based rocket launcher introduces anti-armor lockon capabilities, complemented by a powerful warhead, as well as the ability to dumbfire the weapon against enemy infantry and air. NC use only. <font color="#dc9c36">Optional Lockon: Armor</font>
The Titan-150 HEAT is loaded with high-explosive anti-tank rounds that reload quickly and have balanced effectiveness against enemy armor and personnel. NC use only.
The KSR-35's high-powered 7x65 cartridge is extremely effective at dropping targets at medium range. TR use only.
The Supernova-R PC quickly reloads its high-explosive anti-tank plasma charges that carry balanced effectiveness against armor and infantry. VS use only.
This unassuming three-round burst compact pistol carries surprising stopping power in close quarters. All factions can use NS weapons.

Created with a black metal finish, the imposing NS-15MB has accurate, stable fire at even long distances and reloads quickly. Its reputation as an all-arounder has made it a popular Heavy Assault choice. All factions can use NS weapons.

Crafted in secret, this workshop item has a combat presence similar to the NS Baron G5. While the festive design is painted to resemble older weaponry with wooden pieces, the trees on Auraxis proved too difficult to use as raw material.

Heavy modification has reclassified this NS-30 Vandal as a "non-lethal rifle," capable of firing concussive smart-slugs that slow enemy infantry on impact. While less powerful than the original, the Tranquility boasts higher projectile velocities, and remains suppressed at all times.
The versatile standard-issue NC4 Mag-Shot was the first pistol to utilize Gauss technology. This variant features a unique gold plating.  NC use only.
The powerful AC-X11 was released shortly before Auraxis' global war yet still remains in common use due to its famed reliability and high stopping power. NC use only.

Thanks to its lightweight frame and stabilized barrel, the NS-30 Vandal scout rifle features accurate fire and superior mobility while aimed, making it a common choice for aggressive, mid-range infiltration.
The Skorpios was created as an outdoor SMG to bolster the survivability of the Vanu Sovereignty's frightening Wraith squads when their cloaked Flashes were past running condition.
The C85-H fires a canister of heavy shrapnel that is effective against infantry and light armor. NC use only.

This hard hitting but slower firing SMG is used as an efficient personal defense weapon with a sleek black finish.  Made by Nanite Systems, the leading Auraxis firearms dealer. All factions can use NS weapons.
Known for its lethality in close quarters, the automatic AF-41 Hacksaw's high rate of fire gives it an advantage for point defense scenarios. NC use only.
This black, right-handed NS-10 Burster fires flak rounds which detonate near enemy aircraft, shredding their armor. All factions can use NS weapons.
Originally designed for spec-ops missions that can contain any number of situations, the TRAC-5's adaptability make it a solid choice for any soldier. TR use only.
Originally developed as a stationary turret, the MAX-mounted, multi-barreled M1 Heavy Cycler is capable of shredding apart entire squads without needing to reload. TR use only.
The ML-7 launches unguided rockets that are effective against both infantry and armor. TR use only.
The Charger carbine integrates an overcharging system and unique magazine that increases the stopping power of the first few shots upon freshly reloading the weapon. NC use only.

After a short lock-on period, the Tomcat A2AM platform fires missiles which carry an explosive payload, melting the armor of heavy aircraft, while being less effective against smaller ones. TR use only.
The Serpent VE92's overclocked power core interface allows for an extremely high rate of fire, making it a lethal opponent in close quarters combat. VS use only.
The Basilisk is a 20mm heavy machine gun that effectively damages all targets, especially at close range. All factions can use this weapon.
The G40-F Ranger is an air deterrent flak cannon.  It has a high elevation range and launches 40mm flak rounds that burst when near enemy aircraft. All factions can use this weapon.
The CAS30 Tank Buster armor piercing rounds are highly effective against tanks. All factions can use this weapon.

Exemplary of NC ingenuity and their utter disdain for rules, the aftermarket parts welded into the Brawler not only make it more accurate than typical shotguns, but also illegal to possess in the Terran Republic. Not that they care.

The experimental Lasher X2 fires volatile orbs of plasma that explode on contact with hard surfaces. Field trials have demonstrated its effectiveness at suppressing fire, flushing out enemies and melting infantry. VS use only.
The left handed NS-20 Gorgon is a slow firing heavy machine gun effective at eliminating armored targets, but can challenge close-range infantry as well. All factions can use NS weapons.
The Eclipse easily overshadows its predecessor, the Solstice, as a close-quarters combat king. It comes equipped with an underbarrel plasma shotgun for ambushes and last-ditch scenarios.
The AF-4 Cyclone is a fully automatic submachine gun that has a higher damage output than most weapons in its class. NC use only.
The right handed NS-20 Gorgon is a slow firing heavy machine gun effective at eliminating armored targets, but can challenge close-range infantry as well. All factions can use NS weapons.

After a short lock-on period, the Tomcat A2AM platform fires missiles which carry an explosive payload, melting the armor of heavy aircraft, while being less effective against smaller ones. NC use only.

The opulent NS-11CG is a variant of the 11C, a carbine well known for its stability and all-around performance. The 11CG is also known for all that, as well as looking good. All factions can use NS weapons.

A favorite of Vanu anti-vehicle support soldiers, the unique Revenant battle rifle is excellent at dropping enemies that have bailed to escape their doomed vehicle following a coordinated Lancer strike.
The G30 Walker is a heavy machine gun with a high elevation range and soft point ammunition designed to be more effective against aircraft.  TR use only.
The Saron Laser Cannon is the standard nose cannon for the Vanu Sovereignty's Scythe. Its balanced reload, magazine size, and rate of fire allow it to adapt to any situation. VS use only.
The M30 Mustang Air Hammer fires a barrage of explosive rounds with each shot which are deadly to enemy infantry and lightly armored vehicles. NC use only.

The Duster is equipped with dual 75mm cannons that are able to quickly unload its ten round magazine. Each shot decreases accuracy unless given time to recover; this allows the D-75 to feather accurate shots or bombard a wider area by unloading.

Designed for use by the Terran Republic's top Infiltrator hit squads, the Shuriken's incredible flexibility both close-up and at a distance allowed TR assassins to deal with a multitude of situations they may've not survived otherwise.
The Dragoon is a heavy battle rifle with automatic firing capabilities that hits hard at any range. TR use only.
The Vanquisher's performance is defined by its excellent stopping power over distance, delivered through a low recoil, three-round burst. NC use only.
The powerful Parallax VX3 sniper rifle's heavy-hitting, high velocity plasma projectiles allow for easy long distance shots. VS use only.

Chambered for the powerful .357 magnum cartridge, the snub-nosed Underboss revolver features a faster rate of fire and more controllable recoil than its bigger NS-44 brother. All factions can use this weapon.
The VA39 Spectre semi-automatic sniper rifle is the standard squad support weapon of Vanu Sovereignty Infiltrators. VS use only.
This black left-handed NS-20 Gorgon is a slow firing heavy machine gun effective at eliminating armored targets, but can challenge close-range infantry as well. All factions can use NS weapons.
The gas-powered, semi-automatic FA1 Barrage's narrow shot pattern allows it to put down enemies at ranges beyond other shotguns. TR use only.

Nanite Systems' Annihilator was the first rocket launcher to integrate both air and ground-based lockon capabilities, at cost to its dumbfire capabilities. This variant of the weapon sports a classy gold plating. All factions can use NS weapons. <font color="#dc9c36">Flak detonation. Required Lockon: Aircraft or Armor</font>
The heavy-hitting Eidolon VE33 features accurate semi-automatic fire capable of dropping distant targets with ease. VS use only.
The accurate Heavy Scout Rifle features a higher rate of fire compared to semi-auto sniper rifles. TR use only.
Genudine Dynamics' initial venture into carbines produced the GD-7F. Its high rate of fire makes it an effective weapon in close quarter combat situations. NC use only.
The G30 Vulcan fires armor piercing 30mm rounds capable of damaging heavily armored targets. TR use only.
Created to further enhance the carbine's versatility, the TRAC-5 S can choose between multiple fire modes for firing at distant targets. TR use only.
Aptly named, the  T9 CARV's rate of fire allows it to cut through whole groups of enemies before needing to reload. TR use only.
This platinum variant of the NSX Tanto is a powerful, lightweight carbine which combines precision with versatility, and is most effective in short bursts. All factions can use NS weapons.

Vanu Labs' close-to-midrange Zenith VX-5 uses advanced crystalline structures to significantly reduce weight without compromising on strength. It features both precision hipfire and increased movement speed while aiming.

The SABR-13's two-round burst fire mode was originally developed with ammunition conservation in mind. It has since become popular with marksmen because of its ability to reliably land those two rounds on target from long range. TR use only.

The MKV has an integrated suppressor that prevents the user from showing on the minimap when firing. It features superior bullet velocity and long range stopping power compared to SMGs using optional aftermarket suppressors.

Nanite Systems' first attempts into close-range weaponry resulted in the powerful Baron G5. The tube fed Baron is able to put down targets at longer ranges than typical shotguns thanks to its narrow choke.
The NSX Tanto is a powerful, lightweight carbine which combines precision with versatility, and is most effective in short bursts. All factions can use NS weapons.
This 4th Anniversary Edition of the SMG-46 Armistice submachine gun features an extremely fast rate of fire. TR use only.
The sleek, compact design of the GR-22 improves handling when firing on the move, making it an excellent choice for close quarters combat. NC use only.

The Bishop marksman rifle uses signature ammunition coupled with advanced charge coils to pierce through multiple targets in a single shot. In addition, its heavy damage and controllability make it ideal for long-range engagements. NC use only.
The E540 Halberd fires 85 mm armor-piercing rockets. NC use only.
The Twin-Saron is a high-capacity variant of the standard issue Saron Laser Cannon, meant for use with interceptor variants of the Scythe. VS use only.
The NC6S Gauss SAW's select fire mode gives it incredible adaptability on the field. NC use only.
This special edition of the E540 Halberd mirrors its predecessor's effectiveness, while using a high-density plasma payload. All factions can use this weapon.
The Titan-150-R HEAT is loaded with high-explosive anti-tank rounds that reload quickly and have balanced effectiveness against enemy armor and personnel. NC use only.
The Starfall fires a quick 3 round plasma barrage, meant to strike at unsuspecting vehicles with lighting speed. VS use only.

The Terran Operations Rifle is a favorite amongst TR who feel at home with an all-around performer. Deadly accurate with fast reload assists for its 40 round magazine, the TORQ-9's versatility and ease of use make it a solid choice in combat.
The Diamondback assault rifle is a more aggressive take on the time-tested, and highly adaptable NS-11A.
The Drake is a 20mm heavy machine gun that is effective at damaging all targets. All factions can use this weapon.
The Vortek Rotary is a high damage, close range cannon that shreds enemy fighters with ease. NC use only.
The H-V45 was created with a focus on close quarters mobility. Its light weight does not slow the shooter as much as most other weapons in its class. VS use only.
The Python HEAT carries quick-reloading high-explosive anti-tank rounds that have balanced effectiveness against armor and infantry. All factions can use this weapon.
The standard assault rifle of the Terran Republic, the T1 Cycler features a 40-round magazine and a fast rate of fire, allowing it to remain effective in most situations. TR use only.
The Naginata light machine gun can maintain rounds on medium ranged targets without releasing the trigger, but quickly loses that benefit while moving. All factions can use NS weapons.

Daimyo's three-round magazine contains the headshot killing potential of a bolt-action sniper rifle, with the follow-up potential usually found in semi-automatic snipers. All factions can use NS weapons.

Commissioned by the undying founder of the Vanu Sovereignty for use as his own personal sidearm, Briggs' variant of the Beamer, The Immortal, features an integrated suppressor that retains stopping power even at a distance.

Genudine Dynamic's flexible Hawk rocket launcher can lock onto enemy aircraft, as well as be dumbfired against enemy armor or infantry. NC use only. <font color="#dc9c36">Flak detonation. Optional Lockon: Aircraft</font>
The Ursa features manageable recoil and a high velocity projectile, making it extremely effective at ranges beyond that of other LMGs. VS use only.
The M12 Kobalt is a 50 cal machine gun that is effective against infantry targets. All factions can use this weapon.
The accurate Warden semi-automatic battle rifle is effective at stopping infantry far past the typical LMG or carbine. NC use only.

The Vanu's shadowy VX Labs launched the Terminus VX-9 shortly after joining the war. Engineered with advanced cooling systems that allow for its high rate of fire, the Terminus allows users to hold their ground at close-to-medium ranges.
The 11AB was designed as a customizable weapon system that could adapt to nearly every situation. This variant of the 11A features a sleek black finish. All factions can use NS weapons.

Nanite Systems' Annihilator was the first rocket launcher to integrate both air and ground-based lockon capabilities, at cost to its dumbfire capabilities. All factions can use NS weapons. <font color="#dc9c36">Flak detonation. Required Lockon: Aircraft or Armor</font>

The 11A was designed as a highly adaptable weapons system that could be customized to nearly any situation. Its large, rapid-reload magazine and high-velocity cartridges complement its variety of attachments. All factions can use NS weapons.

This custom-painted variant of the magazine-fed NS-R3 Swarm can switch between low velocity and high velocity rockets which lock onto both ground and air targets, allowing the user to tailor the weapon's tracking capabilities based on the engagement. <font color="#dc9c36">Flak detonation. Required Lockon: Aircraft or Armor</font>

An experimental prototype based off the EM4 resulted in the Moonshot, a hyper-long range bolt-action sniper rifle. While stealth is not the Moonshot's specialty, the speed at which it can drop even the farthest targets offsets its drawbacks.
The Corvus VA55 features low recoil and high accuracy over sustained fire, making it a popular choice for long range engagements. VS use only.
The G40-F Ranger is an air deterrent flak cannon.  It has a high elevation range and launches 40mm flak rounds that burst when near enemy aircraft.  NC use only.
An upgraded version of the successful NC11, the magazine-fed NC14 Bolt Driver is common on the battlefield due to its versatility and high stopping power. NC use only.
The SR-200 embodies the long-distance stopping power of a traditional bolt-action, while retaining versatility through a balanced reload speed and attachment variety. NSO use only.
Ironically nicknamed "Mercy," the latest iteration of the accurate Mobile Rotary Cannon can drop enemy infantry at a distance. TR use only.
The G40-F Ranger is an air deterrent flak cannon.  It has a high elevation range and launches 40mm flak rounds that burst when near enemy aircraft.  TR use only.
The fully automatic NS-61 Emissary operates comfortably at mid-range, thanks to its accuracy and large magazine. All factions can use this weapon.
The powerful Blackheart Quad-Cam crossbow is a lightweight sidearm, capable of silently taking out targets up to medium range with deadly precise bolts.
The Pandora VX25 automatic plasma shotgun is capable of rapidly eliminating opponents in close quarters. VS use only.

Designed for raw power, the Decimator is unmatched in its destructive potential against enemy vehicles and infantry. This variant features classy flames over a black finish. All factions can use NS weapons.
Reverse-engineered from ancient Vanu tech, the Spiker makes use of a standard 2x burst, as well as an alternate firing mode which charges up an armor piercing blast.
The reliable TX1 Repeater is the latest iteration of a firearm design stretching back 300 years. Its 3-round burst fire mode provides considerable stopping power at close range. TR use only.
The versatile Solstice VE3 is an effective carbine suitable for most situations. VS use only.

Genudine Dynamics unveiled the Razor GD-23 in the early 29th century. The Razor quickly became popular due to its high accuracy and controllable recoil, allowing it to outperform other carbines at long distances. NC use only.
The adaptable Jackal SMG has high stopping power in close quarters while remaining easy to control. TR use only.
The versatile M77-B's balance of stopping power, accuracy, and rate of fire make it an excellent choice for Infiltrators that have been provided with limited information for a mission. TR use only.
The awe-inspiring stopping power of the accurate NS-44 Commissioner revolver can put down even mid-range targets with a few well-placed shots. All factions can use this weapon.
The heavy Quasar VM1 was one of the earliest weapons created with discovered Vanu technology. The rapid firing plasma cannon can tear apart enemy foot soldiers with ease. VS use only.
After a short lock-on period, Photon A2A missiles can be fired which carry an explosive payload, melting the armor of heavy aircraft, while being less effective against smaller ones. VS use only.
The Proton II PPA-H fires large orbs of volatile plasma that explode on impact.  The PPA is effective against infantry and light armor. VS use only.
A built-in select fire mode gives users of the Solstice SF the ability to adapt to nearly any scenario. VS use only.

This experimental laser weapon can tear through enemies with sustained fire, but an interesting side effect causes a build up of residual energy while firing that can be harnessed into a devastating blast.
Based on a modified Fracture design, the Gatekeeper retains the feel of its forerunner but incorprorates a faster fire rate and projectile speed while increasing overall accuracy. TR use only.
Designed with distance and accuracy in mind, the TMG-50's manageable recoil allows it to outperform other LMGs at long range. TR use only.
This gold, right-handed NS-10 Burster fires flak rounds which detonate near enemy aircraft, shredding their armor. All factions can use NS weapons.
The P525 Marauder fires 40mm high explosive grenades that are effective against infantry and light armor. TR use only.
The Python AP is loaded with fast-moving armor-piercing rounds that are strong against armored targets, but have little explosive yield. All factions can use this weapon.
Designed for raw power, the Decimator is unmatched in its destructive potential against enemy vehicles and infantry. All factions can use NS weapons.

Built off of the NS-11, the NS-15M1 is an accurate, magazine-fed LMG that performs well in most combat situations. The M1 was accidentally manufactured with a deep black paint, making it somewhat of a collectors item on Auraxis.

The NC05 Jackhammer's stopping power and sustained fire capabilities make it a frightening weapon in close quarters combat. It features a unique burst fire mode that doubles its rate of fire. NC use only.
Designed as an all-purpose sidearm for VS soldiers, the Manticore SX40 is able to perform well in any situation. VS use only.

The M20 Wyvern has superior RPM and faster reload compared to other M20 heavy machine guns but at the cost of a smaller magazine. Like other M20 HMGs, its 20mm rounds are capable of damaging all targets. All factions can use this weapon.
Striking a balance between stopping power and rounds per minute, the fully automatic AF-57 Piston is the preferred shotgun for close-quarters combat. NC use only.
This 4th Anniversary Edition H-V45 was created with a focus on close quarters mobility. Its light weight does not slow the shooter as much as other weapons in its class. VS use only.
Designed in the late 28th century for close quarters and mid-range combat scenarios, the Carnage AR features high hip fire accuracy and an adaptable attachment system. NC use only.
